Scope and baseline

Select 1–2 existing Java/Spring services and define target features or refactors to implement with Kiro.

Capture baseline metrics for similar work done previously (story points, elapsed time, defects, review comments).

Spec creation in Kiro

Use Kiro to turn natural-language requirements into structured requirements and design docs (requirements.md, design.md, tasks.md).

Review and refine specs manually, documenting iteration count and time spent as part of the evaluation.

Implementation and tests (local only)

Let Kiro generate and modify code and tests in a local branch or sandbox workspace, without merging or deploying any artifacts.

Track developer time spent guiding Kiro versus hand-writing code, plus number and type of issues caught during local test runs and code review.

Review and comparison

Perform human code reviews comparing Kiro-generated changes to existing standards for readability, architecture alignment, and test completeness.

Compare Kiro-assisted work to baseline on cycle time, defect density (in local QA), and amount of boilerplate/manual coding saved, summarizing qualitative feedback from developers.
